Overview
	A simple weather application that provides current weather conditions and forecasts for cities in the US.
	This project demonstrates how to fetch and display weather data from a public API.

Features
	Current weather conditions (temperature, humidity, wind speed, etc.)
	5-day weather forecast
	Search by city name
	Responsive design for mobile and desktop
	Weather icons representing current conditions
	AI assistant to give you current conditions & basic weather tips for a selected day

Technologies Used
	HTML5, CSS3, JavaScript
	OpenWeatherMap API
	Node.js, Express.js

Set up
	Clone this repo: git clone https://github.com/lrosend1/COSC-412-WeatherTeam.git
	Navigate to the project directory: cd weather-app
	Install dependencies: npm install
	Get an API key from OpenWeatherMap (free key, don't spend money unnecessarily unless you want to)
	Create a .env file in the root directory and add your API key: API_KEY=your_api_key_here
	Start the application: run node server.js

Usage
	Enter a city name in the search bar
	Press Enter or click the search button
	View current weather and forecast information
	Click "AI Tips" button to get tips

Future Improvements
	Add location detection
	Include more detailed weather data
	Implement temperature unit toggle (Celsius/Fahrenheit)
	Add weather maps or radar
	Improve AI & add a full AI chatbot

Acknowledgments
